cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DB (Database): The paper introduces a new concept of overlay index to be stored in a standard database, alongside regular data and managed by regular software, to complement DBMS capabilities. The paper also proposes a new data structure called DB-tree that realizes an overlay index to support a wide range of custom aggregate range queries as well as Authenticated Data Structures (ADSes), efficiently. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new data structure called DB-tree that realizes an overlay index to support a wide range of custom aggregate range queries as well as Authenticated Data Structures (ADSes), efficiently. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper mentions the need for storing Authenticated Data Structures (ADS) and proposes a solution to support it efficiently. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions that all DB-trees operations can be performed by executing a small number of queries to the DBMS, that can be issued in parallel in one or two query rounds. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper proposes a new data structure called DB-tree that realizes an overlay index to support a wide range of custom aggregate range queries as well as Authenticated Data Structures (ADSes), efficiently.
